Project name: APB monitor in UVM(simple test included)
Author: Lianghao Yuan
Email: yuanlianghao@gmail.com
Date: 06/30/2015

// **********************************************
// Notice:
// 
// The testplan is generated according to the “Coverage cookbook” of Mentor Graphics, 
// and the APB monitor assertion and cover property refers to example offered in the book  
// with minor changes, but completely rebuilt into UVM component.
// **********************************************
// ---------------------------------------
1. Directory structure
// ---------------------------------------
/doc:                      Contains APB3 protocol spec , a testplan for monitor and final 
                           coverage report.
/apb_monitor               Contains Implementation of apb_monitor(apb_monitor_assert_if 
                           for assertion and apb_monitor_cov for coverage) as well as other 
                           UVM component for testbench.
/sim                       Contains Makefile for running the simulation(for Synopsys VCS)
/testbench                 Contains UVM verification components for running test

// ---------------------------------------
2. Usage
// ---------------------------------------
a. Modification of Makefile

Change the UVM_HOME in line 6 to your UVM package location.
Change UVM_VERBOSITY to either UVM_HIGH(default, shows everything) or UVM_LOW (shows nothing).

b. In /sim, type "make" to run basic test

c. To clean all auto-generated files, type "make clean". 


